The MEDIA_TYPE content property for attachments is plagued with client-side issues such as this: https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-37029 . In the event that an attachment is set to the wrong MEDIA_TYPE, the Document File Conversion plugin will actually fail to find the correct converter, thus causing this error:
{code}
2015-06-24 07:42:40,361 ERROR [conversion-thread-0-internal] [conversion.impl.runnable.ConversionRunnable] doWork Format cannot be converted
 -- referer: https://test/display/T/Test?preview=/43619178/43746275/Test.ppt | url: /rest/documentConversion/0.1/conversion/convert/43746275/3 | userName: admin
{code}

This is caused by this: (Confluence Document Conversion 1.9.9)
{code}
 final AbstractConverter converter = getConverter(inFileFormat);
        if (converter == null)
        {
            log.error("Format cannot be converted");
            return;
        }
{code}

Rather than just determining the correct converter to use based on the MEDIA_TYPE property, in the event that a converter cannot be found, we should also check the attachment's extension, and locate a converter based on that

